{"questionId":"26275","questionHtml":"<p>At equilibrium, the concentrations of chlorine and iodine are both 0.02 mol dm<sup>–3</sup>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>Cl<sub>2</sub> (g) +&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>I</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub></math> (g) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇌</mo></math> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>I</mtext></math>Cl (g)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em>K</em><sub>c</sub> = 454</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">What is the concentration of iodine monochloride, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>I</mtext></math>Cl?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>454</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>454</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>454</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>454</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"26275","referenceCode":"22M.1.hl.TZ1.23","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"At equilibrium, the concentrations of chlorine and iodine are both 0.02 mol dm–3. 12Cl2 (g) + 12I2 (g) ⇌ ICl (g) Kc = 454 What is the concentration of iodine monochloride, ICl? A. ","paper":"1","level":"hl","questionNumber":"23","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 7: Equilibrium","7.1 Equilibrium","Core","Topic 7: Equilibrium"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}